## TYPE OF TENANCY

This is a **PRIVATE RESIDENTIAL TENANCY (PRT)** under the Private Housing (Tenancies) (Scotland) Act 2016.

**Important characteristics of a PRT:**
- There is **no fixed end date** - the tenancy continues until either party ends it properly
- The Tenant has security of tenure and can only be evicted on specified grounds
- The Landlord must follow the correct legal procedures and obtain a Tribunal order to evict
- Both parties have specific rights and obligations under the Act

