- Common areas are maintained in reasonable repair, safe and in proper working order
- The property has satisfactory provision for detecting fires and for giving warning in the event of fire or suspected fire
- The property has satisfactory provision for giving warning if carbon monoxide is present

If the Tenant believes the property does not meet the Repairing Standard, they can apply to the local authority or to the First-tier Tribunal.

